question: Will Mitch McConnell still be a Senator on August 4?
description:
This is a market on if Mitch McConnell will still be a United States Senator on August 4, 2023, 12 PM ET. 

This market will resolve to “Yes“ if, at the time of this market's resolution, Mitch McConnell is a United States Senator as officially substantiated by US government sources. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No."

The primary resolution source for this market is https://www.senate.gov/senators/index.html; however, other official government sources may be used.

question: Travis Scott's Utopia over 350k sales week 1?
description:
Travis Scott's new album 'Utopia' is scheduled to be released on July 28, 2023.  

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Travis Scott's new album 'Utopia' has over 350,000 sales in its first week (ending August 3, 2023) according to the finalized version of hitsdailydouble.com's "HITS TOP 50" list. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

This market will resolve according to the figure in the column titled "ALBUMS" once the named list is finalized.  The primary resolution source for this market will be the "HITS TOP 50" list found at https://hitsdailydouble.com/sales_plus_streaming.  

If the chart specified herein is rendered permanently unavailable or does not list 'Utopia', another credible resolution source may be chosen.

question: 2023 FIDE World Cup: Will Magnus Carlsen win top 3?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Magnus Carlsen finishes in the top 3 of the 2023 FIDE World Cup. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No". 

This market may resolve immediately to "No" if it becomes impossible for Magnus Carlsen to win a top 3 position in the 2023 FIDE World Cup based on the rules of the tournament. Likewise, if it becomes a certainty that Magnus Carlsen will win a top 3 position in the 2023 FIDE World Cup, this market will immediately resolve to "Yes".

If the 2023 FIDE World Cup top 3 are not decided by September 30, 2023, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the tournament (e.g. https://worldcup2023.fide.com/), including live footage.

question: Will Biden mention aliens by August 31?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if US President Joe Biden uses the word "alien" or "aliens" in any public, recorded way between July 27 and August 31, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For this market to resolve to "Yes", Biden MUST say "alien" or "aliens" in a video or audio statement. Any context in which "alien" or "aliens" is said will count - e.g. if Biden said "illegal aliens" this market would resolve to "Yes." References to aliens that do not include the word "alien" or "aliens" will not suffice to resolve this market to "Yes." Written statements will not count toward the resolution of this market.

The primary resolution source for this market will be any publicly available recorded or videoed statements by Biden (e.g. video of press conferences, candid videos, etc), however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Will USA win the 2023 Women's World Cup?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if USA is the Champion of FIFA Women's World Cup 2023. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

This market will immediately resolve to “No” if the team is eliminated or otherwise has no path to victory based on the rules of the FIFA Women's World Cup 2023.

If no Champion of FIFA Women's World Cup 2023 is declared by September 30, 2023, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from FIFA (e.g. https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/womens/womensworldcup/australia-new-zealand2023/scores-fixtures), including official footage from the World Cup, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: North Korea nuke by December 31?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Democratic People's Public of Korea (North Korea) detonates a nuclear device in any capacity by December 31, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

This includes offensive usages, nuclear tests, and accidental detonations. Use/launch of a nuclear weapon that fails to detonate, a fake weapon that never detonates, or a dirty bomb that distributes radioactive material by means of a conventional explosion are not sufficient to trigger a "Yes" resolution of this market. Only a successful nuclear detonation initiated by North Korea will result in a "Yes" resolution.

This market may resolve to "Yes" as soon as a nuclear detonation is confirmed by a preponderance of credible reporting.

For the purpose of this market's resolution, determination as to whether a detonation was nuclear will be made by a preponderance of credible reporting.

question: Will Donald Trump be President of the USA on November 30, 2023?
description:
This is a market on if Donald Trump will be President of the United States on November 30, 2023, 12:00 PM ET. 

This market will resolve to “Yes“ if, on the resolution date, Donald Trump is the current President of the United States, officially substantiated by official US government sources, like the links provided as the resolution source. 

If, for any reason, Donald Trump is not the sitting President of the United States on that date/time, this market will resolve to “No". 

The resolution sources are: 1. https://www.loc.gov/rr/print/list/057_chron.html, 2. https://history.house.gov/Institution/Presidents-Coinciding/Presidents-Coinciding/ and 3. https://www.whitehouse.gov/. If any of these 3 sources list Donald Trump officially as the current sitting president on the resolution date, this market will resolve to "Yes".
